{"type":"text","timestamp":1775842201699,"sessionID":"ses_28791b4d1ffeI6r57ziUmO0E2s","part":{"id":"prt_d786f01dc001Py4XE9i45cAG3W","messageID":"msg_d786ed6e3001acl8jBpjuxzY0K","sessionID":"ses_28791b4d1ffeI6r57ziUmO0E2s","type":"text","text":"I'll create the design.md for the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework (AR-004).","time":{"start":1775842201696,"end":1775842201696}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842202101,"sessionID":"ses_28791b4d1ffeI6r57ziUmO0E2s","part":{"id":"prt_d78719064001QgOW3PqTAyn1PT","messageID":"msg_d786ed6e3001acl8jBpjuxzY0K","sessionID":"ses_28791b4d1ffeI6r57ziUmO0E2s","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9b2118dae9474ebe99f9d835b819212a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# pkg/workloadmanager — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework Design\n\n## AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**Size**: M  \n**Purpose**: Provide HTTP API for creating and managing agent runtime sandboxes, implementing session lifecycle management, and integrating with Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── api/\n│   ├── agent_runtime.go       # AgentRuntime CRUD handlers\n│   ├── code_interpreter.go    # CodeInterpreter CRUD handlers\n│   ├── sandbox.go             # Sandbox creation endpoints\n│   ├── middleware.go          # Authentication, logging, recovery\n│   └── types.go               # API request/response types\n├── controller/\n│   ├── agent_runtime.go       # AgentRuntime controller\n│   ├── code_interpreter.go    # CodeInterpreter controller\n│   ├── sandbox_manager.go     # Sandbox lifecycle management\n│   └── session_lifecycle.go   # Session timeout and cleanup\n├── storage/\n│   ├── redis.go               # Redis client wrapper\n│   ├── session_store.go       # Session storage interface\n│   └── metrics.go             # Storage metrics\n├── auth/\n│   ├── jwt.go                 # JWT validation and signing\n│   ├── k8s_auth.go            # Kubernetes TokenReview integration\n│   └── rbac.go                # RBAC enforcement\n├── config/\n│   ├── config.go              # Configuration loading\n│   └── validation.go          # Config validation\n├── server/\n│   ├── server.go              # HTTP server setup\n│   ├── router.go              # Route registration\n│   └── health.go              # Health check endpoints\n└── client/\n    ├── k8s_client.go          # Kubernetes client wrapper\n    ├── runtime_client.go      # AgentCube runtime client\n    └── sandbox_client.go      # Sandbox API client\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     WorkloadManager HTTP Server                  │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Gin HTTP Layer                        │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │           Middleware Chain                         │  │   │\n│  │  │  Auth → Logging → Recovery → RBAC → Metrics        │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │              API Handlers                          │  │   │\n│  │  │  POST /v1/agent-runtime      → CreateSandbox       │  │   │\n│  │  │  POST /v1/code-interpreter   → CreateSandbox       │  │   │\n│  │  │  GET  /v1/sessions/:id       → GetSession          │  │   │\n│  │  │  DELETE /v1/sessions/:id     → DeleteSession       │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         │                     │                     │\n         │                     │                     │\n         ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│  Kubernetes API  │  │     Redis        │  │   Sandbox API    │\n│  (client-go)     │  │   (go-redis)     │  │  (agent-sandbox) │\n│  - CRDs          │  │  - Session store │  │  - Pod CRUD      │\n│  - Pods          │  │  - Activity TTL  │  │  - Secrets       │\n│  - Secrets       │  │  - Metadata      │  │  - TokenReview   │\n└──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nClient Request (Router)\n    ↓\n[Middleware] Auth Validation\n    ↓\n[Middleware] RBAC Check\n    ↓\n[Handler] Parse Request\n    ↓\n[Controller] Validate Spec\n    ↓\n[Controller] Create Session Record\n    ↓\n[Controller] Create Sandbox Pod\n    ↓\n[Controller] Create JWT Token\n    ↓\n[Controller] Update Session Metadata\n    ↓\nResponse: SandboxInfo + SessionID\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### API Request/Response Types\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/api/types.go`\n\n```go\n// CreateSandboxRequest defines the request to create a sandbox\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\" binding:\"required,oneof=AgentRuntime CodeInterpreter\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\n// CreateSandboxResponse defines the response for sandbox creation\ntype CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n    SessionID  string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID  string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName string            `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    EntryPoints []types.EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    CreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt  time.Time          `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n}\n\n// GetSessionRequest defines the request to get session info\ntype GetSessionRequest struct {\n    SessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\n// GetSessionResponse defines the response for session info\ntype GetSessionResponse struct {\n    SessionID    string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID    string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName  string             `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    Kind         string             `json:\"kind\"`\n    Namespace    string             `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Name         string             `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints  []types.EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    LastActivity time.Time          `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n    CreatedAt    time.Time          `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt    time.Time          `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n}\n\n// DeleteSessionRequest defines the request to delete a session\ntype DeleteSessionRequest struct {\n    SessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\n// DeleteSessionResponse defines the response for session deletion\ntype DeleteSessionResponse struct {\n    SessionID string    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    DeletedAt time.Time `json:\"deletedAt\"`\n}\n\n// ErrorResponse defines the error response structure\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error string `json:\"error\"`\n    Code  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// EntryPoint defines a sandbox entry point\ntype EntryPoint struct {\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n    Path     string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n    Port     int32  `json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// SandboxInfo contains sandbox metadata and connection details\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SandboxID    string        `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName  string        `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    SessionID    string        `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    Kind         string        `json:\"kind\"`\n    Namespace    string        `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Name         string        `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints  []EntryPoint  `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    PodIP        string        `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n    NodeName     string        `json:\"nodeName,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt    time.Time     `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt    time.Time     `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    LastActivity time.Time     `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Controller Types\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox_manager.go`\n\n```go\n// SandboxManager manages sandbox lifecycle\ntype SandboxManager struct {\n    k8sClient    kubernetes.Interface\n    runtimeClient runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    sandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n    store        store.Store\n    jwtManager   *auth.JWTManager\n    config       *Config\n}\n\n// SessionMetadata contains session metadata stored in Redis\ntype SessionMetadata struct {\n    SessionID    string    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID    string    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName  string    `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    Kind         string    `json:\"kind\"`\n    Namespace    string    `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Name         string    `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints  []string  `json:\"entryPoints\"` // JSON serialized EntryPoints\n    PodIP        string    `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n    NodeName     string    `json:\"nodeName,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt    time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt    time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n}\n\n// SessionConfig contains session configuration\ntype SessionConfig struct {\n    Timeout         time.Duration\n    MaxDuration     time.Duration\n    KeepAlive       bool\n    RenewalWindow   time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### Configuration Types\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/config/config.go`\n\n```go\n// Config contains WorkloadManager configuration\ntype Config struct {\n    Server   ServerConfig   `json:\"server\"`\n    Redis    RedisConfig    `json:\"redis\"`\n    K8s      K8sConfig      `json:\"k8s\"`\n    Auth     AuthConfig     `json:\"auth\"`\n    Session  SessionConfig  `json:\"session\"`\n    Metrics  MetricsConfig  `json:\"metrics\"`\n}\n\n// ServerConfig contains HTTP server configuration\ntype ServerConfig struct {\n    Port                string        `json:\"port\"`\n    Host                string        `json:\"host\"`\n    ReadTimeout         time.Duration `json:\"readTimeout\"`\n    WriteTimeout        time.Duration `json:\"writeTimeout\"`\n    IdleTimeout         time.Duration `json:\"idleTimeout\"`\n    ShutdownTimeout     time.Duration `json:\"shutdownTimeout\"`\n    EnableProfiling     bool          `json:\"enableProfiling\"`\n    EnablePprof         bool          `json:\"enablePprof\"`\n    MaxHeaderBytes      int           `json:\"maxHeaderBytes\"`\n    EnableTLS           bool          `json:\"enableTLS\"`\n    TLSCertFile         string        `json:\"tlsCertFile\"`\n    TLSKeyFile          string        `json:\"tlsKeyFile\"`\n}\n\n// RedisConfig contains Redis connection configuration\ntype RedisConfig struct {\n    Addr         string        `json:\"addr\"`\n    Password     string        `json:\"password\"`\n    DB           int           `json:\"db\"`\n    PoolSize     int           `json:\"poolSize\"`\n    MinIdleConns int           `json:\"minIdleConns\"`\n    MaxRetries   int           `json:\"maxRetries\"`\n    DialTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"dialTimeout\"`\n    ReadTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"readTimeout\"`\n    WriteTimeout time.Duration `json:\"writeTimeout\"`\n    PoolTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"poolTimeout\"`\n    IdleTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"idleTimeout\"`\n}\n\n// K8sConfig contains Kubernetes client configuration\ntype K8sConfig struct {\n    QPS             float64       `json:\"qps\"`\n    Burst           int           `json:\"burst\"`\n    Timeout         time.Duration `json:\"timeout\"`\n    InClusterConfig bool          `json:\"inClusterConfig\"`\n    Kubeconfig      string        `json:\"kubeconfig\"`\n}\n\n// AuthConfig contains authentication configuration\ntype AuthConfig struct {\n    EnableAuth          bool          `json:\"enableAuth\"`\n    JWTSigningMethod    string        `json:\"jwtSigningMethod\"`\n    JWTExpiration       time.Duration `json:\"jwtExpiration\"`\n    RSAPrivateKeyPath   string        `json:\"rsaPrivateKeyPath\"`\n    RSAPublicKeyPath    string        `json:\"rsaPublicKeyPath\"`\n    EnableK8sTokenReview bool         `json:\"enableK8sTokenReview\"`\n    K8sAPIAudience      string        `json:\"k8sAPIAudience\"`\n}\n\n// SessionConfig contains session management configuration\ntype SessionConfig struct {\n    DefaultTimeout     time.Duration `json:\"defaultTimeout\"`\n    MaxDuration        time.Duration `json:\"maxDuration\"`\n    CleanupInterval    time.Duration `json:\"cleanupInterval\"`\n    KeepAliveEnabled   bool          `json:\"keepAliveEnabled\"`\n    KeepAliveInterval  time.Duration `json:\"keepAliveInterval\"`\n    RenewalWindow      time.Duration `json:\"renewalWindow\"`\n}\n\n// MetricsConfig contains metrics configuration\ntype MetricsConfig struct {\n    Enabled        bool          `json:\"enabled\"`\n    Port           string        `json:\"port\"`\n    Path           string        `json:\"path\"`\n    EnableRuntime  bool          `json:\"enableRuntime\"`\n    EnableProcess  bool          `json:\"enableProcess\"`\n    RuntimeInterval time.Duration `json:\"runtimeInterval\"`\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### HTTP API Endpoints\n\n#### Create Sandbox\n\n**POST** `/v1/agent-runtime` or `/v1/code-interpreter`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n```\nContent-Type: application/json\nAuthorization: Bearer <service-account-token> (optional, when EnableK8sTokenReview is true)\n```\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime|CodeInterpreter\",\n  \"name\": \"python-runtime\",\n  \"namespace\": \"agentcube\"\n}\n```\n\n**Success Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-uuid\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"python-runtime-xxxxx\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [\n    {\n      \"protocol\": \"http\",\n      \"endpoint\": \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n      \"path\": \"/\",\n      \"port\": 8080\n    }\n  ],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-01T01:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 400 Bad Request: Invalid request parameters\n- 401 Unauthorized: Invalid or missing authentication\n- 403 Forbidden: Insufficient permissions\n- 404 Not Found: AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter not found\n- 429 Too Many Requests: Rate limit exceeded\n- 500 Internal Server Error: Server error\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"AgentRuntime 'python-runtime' not found in namespace 'agentcube'\",\n  \"code\": \"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Get Session\n\n**GET** `/v1/sessions/:sessionId`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <service-account-token> (optional)\n```\n\n**Success Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-uuid\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"python-runtime-xxxxx\",\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n  \"namespace\": \"agentcube\",\n  \"name\": \"python-runtime\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [\n    {\n      \"protocol\": \"http\",\n      \"endpoint\": \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n      \"path\": \"/\",\n      \"port\": 8080\n    }\n  ],\n  \"lastActivity\": \"2024-01-01T00:30:00Z\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-01T01:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 404 Not Found: Session not found or expired\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Session 'uuid-v4' not found\",\n  \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Delete Session\n\n**DELETE** `/v1/sessions/:sessionId`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <service-account-token> (optional)\n```\n\n**Success Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n  \"deletedAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:45:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Health Endpoints\n\n**GET** `/health/live`\n```\nStatus: 200 OK\nBody: {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n```\n\n**GET** `/health/ready`\n```\nStatus: 200 OK\nBody: {\"status\":\"ready\"}\n```\n\n**GET** `/health/ready` (when not ready)\n```\nStatus: 503 Service Unavailable\nBody: {\n  \"status\": \"not ready\",\n  \"error\": \"redis connection failed\"\n}\n```\n\n### Storage Interface\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/storage/session_store.go`\n\n```go\n// SessionStore defines the session storage interface\ntype SessionStore interface {\n    // CreateSession creates a new session record\n    CreateSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, metadata *SessionMetadata, ttl time.Duration) error\n    \n    // GetSession retrieves session metadata by session ID\n    GetSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionMetadata, error)\n    \n    // UpdateSessionActivity updates the last activity timestamp\n    UpdateSessionActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, timestamp time.Time) error\n    \n    // DeleteSession removes a session record\n    DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    \n    // ExtendSession extends the session expiration\n    ExtendSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, ttl time.Duration) error\n    \n    // ListSessions lists all active sessions (for admin/debug)\n    ListSessions(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) ([]*SessionMetadata, error)\n    \n    // GetSessionCount returns the count of active sessions\n    GetSessionCount(ctx context.Context) (int64, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Client Interface\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/client/k8s_client.go`\n\n```go\n// K8sClient wraps Kubernetes client operations\ntype K8sClient struct {\n    clientset     kubernetes.Interface\n    runtimeClient runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    sandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n    config        *rest.Config\n}\n\n// CreateSandboxPod creates a sandbox pod from AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter spec\nfunc (c *K8sClient) CreateSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) (*SandboxPod, error)\n\n// GetSandboxPod retrieves a sandbox pod by name\nfunc (c *K8sClient) GetSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*SandboxPod, error)\n\n// DeleteSandboxPod deletes a sandbox pod\nfunc (c *K8sClient) DeleteSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error\n\n// GetAgentRuntime retrieves an AgentRuntime CRD\nfunc (c *K8sClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\n// GetCodeInterpreter retrieves a CodeInterpreter CRD\nfunc (c *K8sClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n\n// WatchSandboxPods watches sandbox pods for changes\nfunc (c *K8sClient) WatchSandboxPods(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (<-chan watch.Event, error)\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/api/errors.go`\n\n```go\n// Common error codes\nconst (\n    ErrorCodeBadRequest                = \"BAD_REQUEST\"\n    ErrorCodeUnauthorized              = \"UNAUTHORIZED\"\n    ErrorCodeForbidden                 = \"FORBIDDEN\"\n    ErrorCodeNotFound                  = \"NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrorCodeSandboxTemplateNotFound   = \"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrorCodeSessionNotFound           = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrorCodeSessionExpired            = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n    ErrorCodeSessionLimitExceeded      = \"SESSION_LIMIT_EXCEEDED\"\n    ErrorCodeRateLimitExceeded         = \"RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED\"\n    ErrorCodeInternalServerError       = \"INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR\"\n    ErrorCodeServiceUnavailable        = \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"\n    ErrorCodeRedisConnectionFailed     = \"REDIS_CONNECTION_FAILED\"\n    ErrorCodeK8sConnectionFailed       = \"K8S_CONNECTION_FAILED\"\n    ErrorCodeJWTSigningFailed          = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n    ErrorCodePodCreationFailed         = \"POD_CREATION_FAILED\"\n)\n\n// WorkloadManagerError defines the WorkloadManager error type\ntype WorkloadManagerError struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n    Cause   error  `json:\"-\"`\n}\n\n// Error implements the error interface\nfunc (e *WorkloadManagerError) Error() string {\n    if e.Cause != nil {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (caused by: %v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Cause)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n}\n\n// Unwrap returns the underlying error\nfunc (e *WorkloadManagerError) Unwrap() error {\n    return e.Cause\n}\n\n// Error constructors\nfunc NewBadRequestError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewUnauthorizedError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewForbiddenError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewNotFoundError(resource, identifier string) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind string) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID string) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewSessionExpiredError(sessionID string) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewSessionLimitExceededError(limit int) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewRateLimitExceededError(message string) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewInternalServerError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\nfunc NewServiceUnavailableError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\n```\n\n### Error Response Mapping\n\n| HTTP Status | Error Code | Condition |\n|-------------|------------|-----------|\n| 400 | BAD_REQUEST | Invalid request parameters |\n| 401 | UNAUTHORIZED | Invalid or missing authentication |\n| 403 | FORBIDDEN | Insufficient RBAC permissions |\n| 404 | SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter not found |\n| 404 | SESSION_NOT_FOUND | Session ID not in store |\n| 404 | SESSION_EXPIRED | Session TTL expired |\n| 429 | SESSION_LIMIT_EXCEEDED | Max sessions per runtime reached |\n| 429 | RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED | Rate limit exceeded |\n| 500 | POD_CREATION_FAILED | Failed to create sandbox pod |\n| 500 | JWT_SIGNING_FAILED | Failed to sign JWT |\n| 500 | INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR | Unexpected server error |\n| 503 | REDIS_CONNECTION_FAILED | Redis connection failed |\n| 503 | K8S_CONNECTION_FAILED | Kubernetes API connection failed |\n| 503 | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE | Service not ready |\n\n### Middleware Error Handling\n\n```go\n// Recovery middleware recovers from panics\nfunc RecoveryMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        defer func() {\n            if err := recover(); err != nil {\n                klog.Errorf(\"Panic recovered: %v\", err)\n                c.JSON(500, ErrorResponse{\n                    Error: \"internal server error\",\n                    Code:  ErrorCodeInternalServerError,\n                })\n                c.Abort()\n            }\n        }()\n        c.Next()\n    }\n}\n\n// Error handling in handlers\nfunc handleError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n    if wmErr, ok := err.(*WorkloadManagerError); ok {\n        statusCode := getHTTPStatusForErrorCode(wmErr.Code)\n        c.JSON(statusCode, ErrorResponse{\n            Error: wmErr.Message,\n            Code:  wmErr.Code,\n        })\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Handle Kubernetes API errors\n    if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        c.JSON(404, ErrorResponse{\n            Error: \"resource not found\",\n            Code:  ErrorCodeNotFound,\n        })\n        return\n    }\n    \n    if apierrors.IsForbidden(err) {\n        c.JSON(403, ErrorResponse{\n            Error: \"access forbidden\",\n            Code:  ErrorCodeForbidden,\n        })\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Default to internal server error\n    klog.Errorf(\"Unexpected error: %v\", err)\n    c.JSON(500, ErrorResponse{\n        Error: \"internal server error\",\n        Code:  ErrorCodeInternalServerError,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/api/handlers_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage api_test\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"net/http\"\n    \"net/http/httptest\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n    . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n    \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/api\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/controller\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/store\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"API Handlers\", func() {\n    var (\n        router      *gin.Engine\n        mockCtrl    *controller.MockSandboxManager\n        mockStore   *store.MockSessionStore\n        authManager *auth.MockAuthManager\n    )\n\n    BeforeEach(func() {\n        gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n        router = gin.New()\n        mockCtrl = controller.NewMockSandboxManager()\n        mockStore = store.NewMockSessionStore()\n        authManager = auth.NewMockAuthManager()\n        \n        api.RegisterRoutes(router, mockCtrl, mockStore, authManager)\n    })\n\n    Describe(\"POST /v1/agent-runtime\", func() {\n        Context(\"Valid request\", func() {\n            It(\"should create sandbox and return session info\", func() {\n                mockCtrl.EXPECT().CreateSandbox(\n                    context.Background(),\n                    \"AgentRuntime\",\n                    \"default\",\n                    \"python-runtime\",\n                ).Return(&controller.SandboxInfo{\n                    SessionID:    \"test-session-id\",\n                    SandboxID:    \"test-sandbox-id\",\n                    SandboxName:  \"python-runtime-abcde\",\n                    EntryPoints:  []api.EntryPoint{...},\n                    CreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n                    ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n                }, nil)\n\n                reqBody := `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"python-runtime\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}`\n                req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", strings.NewReader(reqBody))\n                req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n                resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n                router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n\n                Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n                var respBody api.CreateSandboxResponse\n                json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n                Expect(respBody.SessionID).To(Equal(\"test-session-id\"))\n            })\n        })\n\n        Context(\"Invalid kind\", func() {\n            It(\"should return 400 Bad Request\", func() {\n                reqBody := `{\"kind\":\"InvalidKind\",\"name\":\"python-runtime\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}`\n                req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", strings.NewReader(reqBody))\n                req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n                resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n                router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n\n                Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusBadRequest))\n            })\n        })\n\n        Context(\"AgentRuntime not found\", func() {\n            It(\"should return 404 Not Found\", func() {\n                mockCtrl.EXPECT().CreateSandbox(\n                    context.Background(),\n                    \"AgentRuntime\",\n                    \"default\",\n                    \"nonexistent\",\n                ).Return(nil, api.NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(\"default\", \"nonexistent\", \"AgentRuntime\"))\n\n                reqBody := `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"nonexistent\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}`\n                req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", strings.NewReader(reqBody))\n                req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n                resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n                router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n\n                Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusNotFound))\n                var respBody api.ErrorResponse\n                json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n                Expect(respBody.Code).To(Equal(\"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"))\n            })\n        })\n    })\n\n    Describe(\"GET /v1/sessions/:sessionId\", func() {\n        Context(\"Session exists\", func() {\n            It(\"should return session info\", func() {\n                mockStore.EXPECT().GetSession(\n                    context.Background(),\n                    \"test-session-id\",\n                ).Return(&store.SessionMetadata{\n                    SessionID:    \"test-session-id\",\n                    SandboxID:    \"test-sandbox-id\",\n                    SandboxName:  \"python-runtime-abcde\",\n                    Kind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n                    CreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n                    ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n                    LastActivity: time.Now(),\n                }, nil)\n\n                req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/v1/sessions/test-session-id\", nil)\n                resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n                router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n\n                Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n                var respBody api.GetSessionResponse\n                json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n                Expect(respBody.SessionID).To(Equal(\"test-session-id\"))\n            })\n        })\n\n        Context(\"Session not found\", func() {\n            It(\"should return 404 Not Found\", func() {\n                mockStore.EXPECT().GetSession(\n                    context.Background(),\n                    \"nonexistent-session\",\n                ).Return(nil, store.ErrNotFound)\n\n                req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/v1/sessions/nonexistent-session\", nil)\n                resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n                router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n\n                Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusNotFound))\n                var respBody api.ErrorResponse\n                json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n                Expect(respBody.Code).To(Equal(\"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"))\n            })\n        })\n    })\n})\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage workloadmanager_test\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n    . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest\"\n\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n)\n\nvar (\n    envTest   *envtest.Environment\n    k8sClient client.Client\n    wm        *workloadmanager.WorkloadManager\n)\n\nvar _ = BeforeSuite(func() {\n    err := runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme.Scheme)\n    Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n    envTest = &envtest.Environment{\n        CRDDirectoryPaths: []string{\"../../manifests/charts/base/crds\"},\n    }\n\n    cfg, err := envTest.Start()\n    Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n    k8sClient, err = client.New(cfg, client.Options{Scheme: scheme.Scheme})\n    Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n})\n\nvar _ = AfterSuite(func() {\n    err := envTest.Stop()\n    Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"WorkloadManager Integration\", func() {\n    Context(\"Sandbox lifecycle\", func() {\n        It(\"should create sandbox from AgentRuntime\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n            namespace := \"default\"\n            \n            art := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n                ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                    Name:      \"python-runtime\",\n                    Namespace: namespace,\n                },\n                Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                    SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n                    MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n                    PodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n                        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n                            Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n                                {\n                                    Name:  \"agent\",\n                                    Image: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n                                },\n                            },\n                        },\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n\n            err := k8sClient.Create(ctx, art)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n            resp, err := wm.CreateSandbox(ctx, &workloadmanager.CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n                Name:      \"python-runtime\",\n                Namespace: namespace,\n            })\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            Expect(resp.SessionID).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n            Expect(resp.SandboxName).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n        }, SpecTimeout(30*time.Second))\n\n        It(\"should cleanup expired sessions\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n            sessionID := \"test-expired-session\"\n            \n            err := wm.CreateSessionRecord(ctx, sessionID, &workloadmanager.SandboxInfo{\n                SessionID:    sessionID,\n                SandboxID:    \"sandbox-id\",\n                SandboxName:  \"test-sandbox\",\n                ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n            })\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n            Eventually(func() bool {\n                _, err := wm.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)\n                return err == nil\n            }, 10*time.Second, time.Second).Should(BeFalse())\n        }, SpecTimeout(30*time.Second))\n    })\n})\n```\n\n### E2E Tests\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/workloadmanager_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage e2e\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n    . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/test/e2e/framework\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"WorkloadManager E2E\", func() {\n    f := framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"workloadmanager\")\n\n    Context(\"Create and manage sandboxes\", func() {\n        It(\"should create sandbox from AgentRuntime and route traffic\", func() {\n            ctx := context.Background()\n            \n            art := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n                ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                    Name:      \"e2e-python-runtime\",\n                    Namespace: f.Namespace.Name,\n                },\n                Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                    SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 5 * time.Minute},\n                    MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 1 * time.Hour},\n                    PodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n                        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n                            Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n                                {\n                                    Name:  \"agent\",\n                                    Image: \"ghcr.io/volcano-sh/python-agent:latest\",\n                                    Ports: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainerPort{\n                                        {ContainerPort: 8080},\n                                    },\n                                },\n                            },\n                        },\n                    },\n                },\n            }\n\n            err := f.Client.Create(ctx, art)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n            // Create sandbox via WorkloadManager API\n            resp, err := f.WMClient.CreateSandbox(ctx, &CreateSandboxRequest{\n                Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n                Name:      \"e2e-python-runtime\",\n                Namespace: f.Namespace.Name,\n            })\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n            // Verify sandbox pod is created\n            Eventually(func() bool {\n                pod, err := f.ClientSet.CoreV1().Pods(f.Namespace.Name).Get(\n                    ctx, resp.SandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{},\n                )\n                if err != nil {\n                    return false\n                }\n                return pod.Status.Phase == \"Running\"\n            }, 2*time.Minute, 5*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n\n            // Verify session is stored\n            session, err := f.WMClient.GetSession(ctx, resp.SessionID)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            Expect(session.SessionID).To(Equal(resp.SessionID))\n\n            // Test routing through router\n            req := f.NewRequest(\"GET\", f.RouterURL+\"/v1/namespaces/\"+f.Namespace.Name+\"/agent-runtimes/e2e-python-runtime/invocations/test\", nil)\n            req.Header.Set(\"x-agentcube-session-id\", resp.SessionID)\n            \n            httpResponse, err := f.HTTPClient.Do(req)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            Expect(httpResponse.StatusCode).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n        })\n    })\n})\n```\n\n## Metrics and Observability\n\n### Prometheus Metrics\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/storage/metrics.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n    // Session metrics\n    metricSessionCount = \"workloadmanager_sessions_total\"\n    metricSessionCreated = \"workloadmanager_sessions_created_total\"\n    metricSessionDeleted = \"workloadmanager_sessions_deleted_total\"\n    metricSessionExpired = \"workloadmanager_sessions_expired_total\"\n    \n    // Sandbox metrics\n    metricSandboxCreated = \"workloadmanager_sandboxes_created_total\"\n    metricSandboxFailed = \"workloadmanager_sandboxes_failed_total\"\n    metricSandboxActive = \"workloadmanager_sandboxes_active\"\n    \n    // Request metrics\n    metricRequestDuration = \"workloadmanager_request_duration_seconds\"\n    metricRequestTotal = \"workloadmanager_requests_total\"\n    metricRequestErrors = \"workloadmanager_request_errors_total\"\n    \n    // Storage metrics\n    metricStorageLatency = \"workloadmanager_storage_latency_seconds\"\n    metricStorageErrors = \"workloadmanager_storage_errors_total\"\n    \n    // Kubernetes metrics\n    metricK8sAPILatency = \"workloadmanager_k8s_api_latency_seconds\"\n    metricK8sAPIErrors = \"workloadmanager_k8s_api_errors_total\"\n)\n\nvar (\n    sessionCount = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: metricSessionCount,\n            Help: \"Total number of active sessions\",\n        },\n        []string{\"kind\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n    )\n    \n    sessionCreated = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: metricSessionCreated,\n            Help: \"Total number of sessions created\",\n        },\n        []string{\"kind\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n    )\n    \n    sandboxCreated = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: metricSandboxCreated,\n            Help: \"Total number of sandboxes created\",\n        },\n        []string{\"kind\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n    )\n    \n    requestDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    metricRequestDuration,\n            Help:    \"Request duration in seconds\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        },\n        []string{\"method\", \"endpoint\", \"status\"},\n    )\n)\n\nfunc init() {\n    prometheus.MustRegister(sessionCount)\n    prometheus.MustRegister(sessionCreated)\n    prometheus.MustRegister(sandboxCreated)\n    prometheus.MustRegister(requestDuration)\n}\n```\n\n### Logging\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/server/logging.go`\n\n```go\n// Structured logging configuration\ntype LoggingConfig struct {\n    Level      string `json:\"level\"`\n    Format     string `json:\"format\"` // json or text\n    Output     string `json:\"output\"` // stdout, stderr, or file path\n    MaxSize    int    `json:\"maxSize\"`\n    MaxAge     int    `json:\"maxAge\"`\n    MaxBackups int    `json:\"maxBackups\"`\n}\n\n// Log fields for structured logging\nconst (\n    LogFieldSessionID    = \"session_id\"\n    LogFieldSandboxID    = \"sandbox_id\"\n    LogFieldSandboxName  = \"sandbox_name\"\n    LogFieldKind         = \"kind\"\n    LogFieldNamespace    = \"namespace\"\n    LogFieldName         = \"name\"\n    LogFieldUserID       = \"user_id\"\n    LogFieldMethod       = \"method\"\n    LogFieldPath         = \"path\"\n    LogFieldStatusCode   = \"status_code\"\n    LogFieldDuration     = \"duration_ms\"\n    LogFieldError        = \"error\"\n    LogFieldErrorCode    = \"error_code\"\n)\n\n// Log helper functions\nfunc LogSessionCreated(ctx context.Context, sessionID, sandboxID, kind, namespace, name string) {\n    klog.InfoS(\"Session created\",\n        LogFieldSessionID, sessionID,\n        LogFieldSandboxID, sandboxID,\n        LogFieldKind, kind,\n        LogFieldNamespace, namespace,\n        LogFieldName, name,\n    )\n}\n\nfunc LogSessionDeleted(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) {\n    klog.InfoS(\"Session deleted\",\n        LogFieldSessionID, sessionID,\n    )\n}\n\nfunc LogRequest(ctx context.Context, method, path string, statusCode int, duration time.Duration) {\n    klog.InfoS(\"Request completed\",\n        LogFieldMethod, method,\n        LogFieldPath, path,\n        LogFieldStatusCode, statusCode,\n        LogFieldDuration, duration.Milliseconds(),\n    )\n}\n\nfunc LogError(ctx context.Context, err error, fields ...interface{}) {\n    if wmErr, ok := err.(*WorkloadManagerError); ok {\n        klog.ErrorS(err, \"WorkloadManager error\",\n            append(fields,\n                LogFieldErrorCode, wmErr.Code,\n                LogFieldError, wmErr.Message,\n            )...,\n        )\n    } else {\n        klog.ErrorS(err, \"Unexpected error\", fields...)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Security\n\n### Authentication\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/auth/k8s_auth.go`\n\n```go\n// K8sAuthenticator validates Kubernetes service account tokens\ntype K8sAuthenticator struct {\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n    audience   string\n}\n\n// Authenticate validates a service account token using TokenReview API\nfunc (a *K8sAuthenticator) Authenticate(ctx context.Context, token string) (*AuthenticationInfo, error) {\n    tokenReview := &authenticationv1.TokenReview{\n        Spec: authenticationv1.TokenReviewSpec{\n            Token:     token,\n            Audiences: []string{a.audience},\n        },\n    }\n\n    resp, err := a.clientset.AuthenticationV1().TokenReviews().Create(ctx, tokenReview, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"token review failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    if !resp.Status.Authenticated {\n        return nil, NewUnauthorizedError(\"token authentication failed\", nil)\n    }\n\n    return &AuthenticationInfo{\n        Username: resp.Status.User.Username,\n        UID:      resp.Status.User.UID,\n        Groups:   resp.Status.User.Groups,\n        Extra:    resp.Status.User.Extra,\n    }, nil\n}\n\n// AuthenticationInfo contains authenticated user information\ntype AuthenticationInfo struct {\n    Username string\n    UID      string\n    Groups   []string\n    Extra    map[string]authenticationv1.ExtraValue\n}\n```\n\n### Authorization (RBAC)\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/auth/rbac.go`\n\n```go\n// Authorizer enforces RBAC policies\ntype Authorizer struct {\n    subjectAccessReviewClient authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReviewInterface\n}\n\n// CanCreateSandbox checks if the user can create a sandbox for the given runtime\nfunc (a *Authorizer) CanCreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, user, namespace, name string) (bool, error) {\n    sar := &authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReview{\n        Spec: authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReviewSpec{\n            User:   user,\n            ResourceAttributes: &authorizationv1.ResourceAttributes{\n                Group:     \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n                Resource:  \"agentruntimes\",\n                Verb:      \"get\",\n                Namespace: namespace,\n                Name:      name,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n\n    resp, err := a.subjectAccessReviewClient.Create(ctx, sar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return false, err\n    }\n\n    return resp.Status.Allowed, nil\n}\n\n// CanDeleteSession checks if the user can delete a session\nfunc (a *Authorizer) CanDeleteSession(ctx context.Context, user, sessionID string) (bool, error) {\n    // Sessions are stored in Redis, so we check if the user has permission\n    // to manage sandboxes in the namespace associated with the session\n    sar := &authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReview{\n        Spec: authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReviewSpec{\n            User: user,\n            NonResourceAttributes: &authorizationv1.NonResourceAttributes{\n                Verb:     \"delete\",\n                Path:     fmt.Sprintf(\"/v1/sessions/%s\", sessionID),\n            },\n        },\n    }\n\n    resp, err := a.subjectAccessReviewClient.Create(ctx, sar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return false, err\n    }\n\n    return resp.Status.Allowed, nil\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Signing\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/auth/jwt.go`\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles JWT token generation and validation\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    expiration time.Duration\n    issuer     string\n}\n\n// GenerateToken generates a JWT token for sandbox access\nfunc (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n    now := time.Now()\n    \n    standardClaims := jwt.MapClaims{\n        \"exp\": now.Add(j.expiration).Unix(),\n        \"iat\": now.Unix(),\n        \"iss\": j.issuer,\n    }\n    \n    // Merge custom claims\n    for k, v := range claims {\n        standardClaims[k] = v\n    }\n    \n    token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, standardClaims)\n    \n    tokenString, err := token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sign token: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    return tokenString, nil\n}\n\n// ValidateToken validates a JWT token and returns the claims\nfunc (j *JWTManager) ValidateToken(tokenString string) (jwt.MapClaims, error) {\n    token, err := jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n        if _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected signing method: %v\", token.Header[\"alg\"])\n        }\n        return j.publicKey, nil\n    })\n    \n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse token: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    if claims, ok := token.Claims.(jwt.MapClaims); ok && token.Valid {\n        return claims, nil\n    }\n    \n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid token\")\n}\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Go Module Dependencies\n\n```go\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n\ngo 1.24\n\nrequire (\n    github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n    github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.7.0\n    github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1\n    k8s.io/api v0.32.1\n    k8s.io/apimachinery v0.32.1\n    k8s.io/client-go v0.32.1\n    sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.2\n    sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.6.0\n    github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.20.5\n    k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n    github.com/spf13/cobra v1.8.1\n    github.com/spf13/viper v1.19.0\n)\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default | Required |\n|----------|-------------|---------|----------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Redis server address | `localhost:6379` | Yes |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Redis password | empty | No |\n| `REDIS_DB` | Redis database number | `0` | No |\n| `KUBECONFIG` | Path to kubeconfig file | `~/.kube/config` | No (in-cluster) |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` | HTTP server port | `8080` | No |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_HOST` | HTTP server host | `0.0.0.0` | No |\n| `ENABLE_TLS` | Enable TLS | `false` | No |\n| `TLS_CERT_FILE` | TLS certificate file path | empty | No |\n| `TLS_KEY_FILE` | TLS private key file path | empty | No |\n| `JWT_EXPIRATION` | JWT token expiration duration | `5m` | No |\n| `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | Default session timeout | `15m` | No |\n| `MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | Maximum session duration | `8h` | No |\n| `ENABLE_K8S_AUTH` | Enable Kubernetes token authentication | `true` | No |\n| `K8S_API_AUDIENCE` | Kubernetes API audience for token review | `agentcube` | No |\n| `METRICS_ENABLED` | Enable Prometheus metrics | `true` | No |\n| `METRICS_PORT` | Metrics server port | `9090` | No |\n| `LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level | `info` | No |\n| `LOG_FORMAT` | Log format (json/text) | `json` | No |\n\n### Kubernetes RBAC Permissions\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nrules:\n  # AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n  \n  # Sandbox resources\n  - apiGroups: [\"agent-sandbox.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxes\", \"sandboxclaims\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"delete\", \"watch\"]\n  \n  # Pod management\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"pods\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"watch\"]\n  \n  # Secret management\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n  \n  # Authentication\n  - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\"]\n  \n  # Authorization\n  - apiGroups: [\"authorization.k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"subjectaccessreviews\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\"]\n  \n  # ConfigMaps and ConfigMap volume sources\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n```\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With Router\n\nThe Router calls the WorkloadManager HTTP API:\n\n```\nPOST {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime\nPOST {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter\nGET {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/sessions/{sessionID}\nDELETE {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/sessions/{sessionID}\n```\n\nThe WorkloadManager returns `CreateSandboxResponse` with session and sandbox information.\n\n### With Session Store\n\nThe WorkloadManager uses the Redis session store:\n\n```go\nstore.Storage() // Returns shared store client\nstore.CreateSession(ctx, sessionID, metadata, ttl)\nstore.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)\nstore.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, timestamp)\nstore.DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID)\n```\n\n### With Kubernetes API\n\nThe WorkloadManager uses the generated client-go:\n\n```go\nruntimeClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1()\nagentRuntime, err := runtimeClient.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, opts)\npod, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, opts)\n```\n\n### With Sandbox API\n\nThe WorkloadManager uses the agent-sandbox API:\n\n```go\nsandboxClient := agentv1.NewForConfig(config)\nsandbox, err := sandboxClient.Sandboxes(namespace).Create(ctx, &sandbox, opts)\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n### API Documentation\n\nOpenAPI/Swagger documentation should be generated and served at `/swagger` endpoint:\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/swaggo/gin-swagger\"\nimport \"github.com/swaggo/files\"\n\n// In router setup\nr.GET(\"/swagger/*any\", ginSwagger.WrapHandler(swaggerFiles.Handler))\n```\n\n### Configuration Reference\n\nAll configuration options should be documented in `docs/configuration.md` with:\n- Default values\n- Environment variable names\n- CLI flag names\n- Description of each option\n- Examples\n\n### Examples\n\n**Example AgentRuntime** (`examples/agentruntime.yaml`):\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: python-agent\n  namespace: agentcube\nspec:\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  podTemplate:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: python-agent\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: agent\n        image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/python-agent:latest\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n        resources:\n          limits:\n            cpu: \"500m\"\n            memory: \"512Mi\"\n          requests:\n            cpu: \"100m\"\n            memory: \"128Mi\"\n```\n\n**Example API Usage**:\n\n```bash\n# Create sandbox\ncurl -X POST http://workloadmanager:8080/v1/agent-runtime \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n    \"name\": \"python-agent\",\n    \"namespace\": \"agentcube\"\n  }'\n\n# Get session\ncurl http://workloadmanager:8080/v1/sessions/{sessionID}\n\n# Delete session\ncurl -X DELETE http://workloadmanager:8080/v1/sessions/{sessionID}\n```\n\n## Version Migration Strategy\n\nFuture migration from v1alpha1 to v1beta1/v1:\n\n1. Update API version in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1beta1/`\n2. Implement conversion functions between versions\n3. Maintain backward compatibility during migration period\n4. Update CRD to serve both versions\n5. Migrate controllers and clients incrementally\n6. Deprecate v1alpha1 after stabilization period","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/deepcopy.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":22,"character":1},"end":{"line":22,"character":7}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#S1023"},"source":"S1023","message":"redundant return statement"},{"range":{"start":{"line":52,"character":1},"end":{"line":52,"character":7}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescr